            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-5773",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "curl: libcurl: Wrong file transfer due to incorrect SMB connection reuse"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "libcurl might in some circumstances reuse the wrong connection for SMB(S)\ntransfers.\n\nlibcurl features a pool of recent connections so that subsequent requests can\nreuse an existing connection to avoid overhead.\n\nWhen reusing a connection a range of criteria must be met. Due to a logical\nerror in the code, a network transfer operation that was requested by an\napplication could wrongfully reuse an existing SMB connection to the same\nserver that was using a different 'share' than the new subsequent transfer\nshould.\n\nThis could in unlucky situations lead to the download of the wrong file or the\nupload of a file to the wrong place. When this happens, the same credentials\nare used and the server name is the same."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-5773",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-5773\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: libcurl4t64\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-5773](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-5773)\nlibcurl might in some circumstances reuse the wrong connection for SMB(S)\ntransfers.\n\nlibcurl features a pool of recent connections so that subsequent requests can\nreuse an existing connection to avoid overhead.\n\nWhen reusing a connection a range of criteria must be met. Due to a logical\nerror in the code, a network transfer operation that was requested by an\napplication could wrongfully reuse an existing SMB connection to the same\nserver that was using a different 'share' than the new subsequent transfer\nshould.\n\nThis could in unlucky situations lead to the download of the wrong file or the\nupload of a file to the wrong place. When this happens, the same credentials\nare used and the server name is the same.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-5773**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|libcurl4t64||[CVE-2026-5773](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-5773)|\n\nlibcurl might in some circumstances reuse the wrong connection for SMB(S)\ntransfers.\n\nlibcurl features a pool of recent connections so that subsequent requests can\nreuse an existing connection to avoid overhead.\n\nWhen reusing a connection a range of criteria must be met. Due to a logical\nerror in the code, a network transfer operation that was requested by an\napplication could wrongfully reuse an existing SMB connection to the same\nserver that was using a different 'share' than the new subsequent transfer\nshould.\n\nThis could in unlucky situations lead to the download of the wrong file or the\nupload of a file to the wrong place. When this happens, the same credentials\nare used and the server name is the same."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 7.5,
                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N",
