            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-6276",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "curl: libcurl: Information disclosure due to cookie leak when reusing connections with custom Host headers"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Using libcurl, when a custom `Host:` header is first set for an HTTP request\nand a second request is subsequently done using the same *easy handle* but\nwithout the custom `Host:` header set, the second request would use stale\ninformation and pass on cookies meant for the first host in the second\nrequest. Leak them."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-6276",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-6276\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: libcurl4t64\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-6276](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-6276)\nUsing libcurl, when a custom `Host:` header is first set for an HTTP request\nand a second request is subsequently done using the same *easy handle* but\nwithout the custom `Host:` header set, the second request would use stale\ninformation and pass on cookies meant for the first host in the second\nrequest. Leak them.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-6276**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|libcurl4t64||[CVE-2026-6276](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-6276)|\n\nUsing libcurl, when a custom `Host:` header is first set for an HTTP request\nand a second request is subsequently done using the same *easy handle* but\nwithout the custom `Host:` header set, the second request would use stale\ninformation and pass on cookies meant for the first host in the second\nrequest. Leak them."
              },
              "properties": {
