              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw in curl's cookie parsing logic allows a malicious HTTP server to set \"super cookies\" that bypass the Public Suffix List check. This enables an attacker-controlled origin to inject cookies that curl will subsequently scope and transmit to unrelated third-party domains."
