              "id": "CVE-2026-9080",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": ""
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Calling `curl_easy_pause()` within the event-based `CURLMOPT_SOCKETFUNCTION` callback triggers a use-after-free vulnerability, where libcurl attempts to store a flag using a dangling struct pointer immediately after that pointer's memory has been freed."
              },
