            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-11850",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "krb5: krb5: integer underflow in berval2tl_data() leads to heap out-of-bounds read"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An integer underflow vulnerability was found in MIT krb5 in the berval2tl_data() function in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c. The function performs an unsigned subtraction (bv_len - 2) without a prior bounds check. When bv_len is 0 or 1, the subtraction wraps to a large value which is then truncated to uint16_t, yielding 0xFFFE (65534) or 0xFFFF (65535). The subsequent malloc succeeds and memcpy reads up to 65534 bytes from a 0-1 byte buffer, resulting in a heap out-of-bounds read.\nThe attack vector involves a malicious or compromised LDAP KDB backend returning a krbExtraData attribute with bv_len \u003c 2, triggering the underflow when the KDC or kadmind reads principal data."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-11850",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-11850\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: libkrb5support0\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-11850](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-11850)\nAn integer underflow vulnerability was found in MIT krb5 in the berval2tl_data() function in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c. The function performs an unsigned subtraction (bv_len - 2) without a prior bounds check. When bv_len is 0 or 1, the subtraction wraps to a large value which is then truncated to uint16_t, yielding 0xFFFE (65534) or 0xFFFF (65535). The subsequent malloc succeeds and memcpy reads up to 65534 bytes from a 0-1 byte buffer, resulting in a heap out-of-bounds read.\nThe attack vector involves a malicious or compromised LDAP KDB backend returning a krbExtraData attribute with bv_len \u003c 2, triggering the underflow when the KDC or kadmind reads principal data.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-11850**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|libkrb5support0||[CVE-2026-11850](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-11850)|\n\nAn integer underflow vulnerability was found in MIT krb5 in the berval2tl_data() function in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c. The function performs an unsigned subtraction (bv_len - 2) without a prior bounds check. When bv_len is 0 or 1, the subtraction wraps to a large value which is then truncated to uint16_t, yielding 0xFFFE (65534) or 0xFFFF (65535). The subsequent malloc succeeds and memcpy reads up to 65534 bytes from a 0-1 byte buffer, resulting in a heap out-of-bounds read.\nThe attack vector involves a malicious or compromised LDAP KDB backend returning a krbExtraData attribute with bv_len \u003c 2, triggering the underflow when the KDC or kadmind reads principal data."
              },
